Building with MinGW/MSYS:
    Build libmc--c:
    set HOME environment variable to your development home directory
    extract libmc--c to $HOME/
    cd libmc--c
    make
    make install
    
    Build test app:
    cd test
    make


Using:
    Copy "terrain.png" to $HOME/libmc--c/bin.
    Copy shared libraries to $HOME/libmc--c/bin:
        DevIL.dll
        ILU.dll
        ILUT.dll
        sfml-graphics.dll
        sfml-system.dll
        sfml-window.dll
        libgcc DLL
        libstdc++ DLL
    
    cd $HOME/libmc--c/bin
    mc--c
    
    This test program will preview how each block will look with this skin,
    using libmc--c.
    
Controls:
    North       Mouse-wheel up, Up-arrow, W
    South       Mouse-wheel down, Down-arrow, S
    West        Left-drag left, Left-arrow, A
    East        Left-drag right, Right-arrow, D
    Down        Left-drag down, Home
    Up          Left-drag up, PageUp
    Turn left   Right-click drag, End, Q
    Turn right  Right-click drag, PageDown, E
    Respawn     Middle-click
    Tree color  R, G, B
    Quit        Esc

Thanks to the following people for testing:
    vLK
